author: struberg
msg: This commit cleans up a lot old stuff and improves the caching
for EL evaluations heavily. We now cache every resolved Bean proxy
until the end of the request. This doesn't hurt even if the managed beans
have a shorter lifecycle, because the proxy will take care of such scenarios!

author: struberg
msg: OWB-414 drop doPrivileged from ClassLoader detection
is a highly expensive task. Doing this in the most heavy spot
of OWB means a measured performance penalty from 20 to 30%.
Given the fact that OWB (even if running in Geronimo or any
other multi ClassLoader scenario) will always get bootstrapped
in the context of a WebApp, we should not get any problems
